The first game of the year at the newly renovated Bulldog Stadium is tonight! The Star City Bulldogs will take on the Stuttgart Ricebirds with a 7:00 p.m. kickoff. Tickets are $5.00 at the gate, if you do not have a Season Pass, and will be sold until we reach capacity according to Arkansas Department of Health guidelines. Please wear a mask and social distance so our students can continue to play. If you’re unable to join us in person, you can view this game on Channel 42 KARZ or via our livestream on the Star City Schools YouTube channel!

Thank you all for your support!

shared_text:
Bright Futures Star City
August 28 at 10:15 AM ·

As we are organizing our supply closet for this school year we have noticed that we are running low on particular items, but are limited on additional storage space. This leads us to ask for what may seem like an unusual request. If you would be willing, we would love to have some gift cards to local stores to purchase emergency items (such as undergarments, etc..), as the need arises. This would allow us to easily purchase these items in the correct size as needed as opposed to stocking some of all sizes for Pre-K through High School. If you would like to donate, please bring any gift cards to the high school office.
text:

Star City School District will utilize virtual learning for 8/27/20. Students in grades 3-12 will bring home school devices to complete assignments. Students in grades K-2 and ABC will complete paper packets.

Buses will run at 10:30 today. Please make arrangements to have someone available to meet your students at the bus stop.

SCSD is actively monitoring the weather situation and will continue to make adjustments as necessary. If we plan to continue virtual learning beyond today, we will notify parents/guardians as soon as possible.

UAM Alumni & Friends
August 20 at 10:00 AM ·

Congratulations to #UAMAlum April Reeves (BS ‘10/MAT ’18).

Mrs. Reeves is beginning her fifth year of teaching. She is employed with the Star City School District as the high school physical science and environmental science teacher. In 2019, Mrs. Reeves completed her M.Ed in Learning Systems Technology at UALR specializing in the delivery of online education. She is currently in the process of applying to earn her doctorate in education but has not yet decided on a specialization. #UAMSuccess #UnitedbyUAM #UAMemories

Star City Ladydog Basketball
August 19 at 9:10 AM ·

Ladydog Senior Spotlight: Janiya Johnson

Nae is a 2 time All-Conference, 2 time All-State, and a State Finals MVP. Nae is an explosive point guard that can take over a game. She has a few college offers currently. Nae averaged 15 points per game this last season as well as 3.4 steals a game. She also averaged 4.9 rebounds a game.

shared_text:
UAM Alumni & Friends
August 13 at 10:00 AM ·

Congratulations to #UAMAlum Lezeme Winn (BS ‘05/MAT ’08).

Mr. Winn was recently hired as the principal at Star City High School. Prior to joining the Star City School District, Mr. Winn spent the last 11 years in the Dumas School District in a variety of roles as a teacher, coach and most recently as DJHS Asst. Principal and the district’s athletic director. During his time at UAM Mr. Winn served as the SGA president and was a member of the Sigma Tau Gamma fraternity. Mr. Winn also served in the US Marine Corp reserves during his time at UAM and was deployed to Iraq in support of Operation Enduring Freedom in 2003. #UAMSuccess #UnitedbyUAM #UAMemories
